# {{ cfg.agent.target_suffix | capitalize }}
Use `{{ cfg.agent.display_name }}` in Podman or Docker container, to avoid potential dangerous actions.

- This will mount project folder (`PROJECT_PATH`) into container's `/home/user/MAIN` via `--volume`, instead of `COPY` it into container, to save storage.
- `git` is not configured on purpose, to prevent `{{ cfg.agent.display_name }}` from doing someting dangerous.

> [!NOTE]
> Use via the installed launchers (rendered tree lives at `~/.local/share/container-templates/{{ cfg.name }}/`):
> ```sh
> # run the {{ cfg.agent.display_name }} agent under default runtime (crun)
> cd ~/my_project && c-{{ cfg.name }}-crun {{ cfg.agent.target_suffix }}
>
> # same, but inside a libkrun microVM (stronger isolation, no `podman exec`)
> cd ~/my_project && c-{{ cfg.name }}-krun {{ cfg.agent.target_suffix }}
>
> # first-time setup (build image + start container)
> cd ~/my_project && c-{{ cfg.name }}-crun init
>
> # get a shell inside the container
> c-{{ cfg.name }}-crun zsh-user
>
> # advanced: invoke container.sh directly (skip launcher)
> PROJECT_NAME=foo PROJECT_PATH=~/foo RUNTIME=crun \
>     ~/.local/share/container-templates/{{ cfg.name }}/container.sh init
